# Governance — <%= appName %>

Company engineering standards for **<%= company %>**.

## Layout

```
src/governance/
  policy/
  rules/
  checker/
tests/governance/
company-policy.json
GOVERNANCE.md
```

## Required standards

Every project must include:

| Requirement | Rule ID |
|-------------|---------|
| PostgreSQL | `req-database-postgres` |
| Docker | `req-docker` |
| Authentication | `req-auth` |
| RBAC | `req-rbac` |
| Security platform | `req-security` |
| Audit logs | `req-audit` |
| Automated tests | `req-tests` |
| CI/CD | `req-cicd` |
| Documentation | `req-docs` |

## CLI

```bash
my governance setup
my governance check
```

## Usage

```ts
import { registerGovernance } from './src/governance/index.js';

const governance = registerGovernance();
const report = governance.check({
  projectName: '<%= appName %>',
  database: 'postgresql',
  features: { docker: true, auth: true, rbac: true, security: true, audit: true, testing: true },
  scripts: { test: 'vitest run' },
  existingPaths: ['Dockerfile', 'src/security', 'src/audit', 'tests', '.github/workflows', 'README.md'],
});

console.log(report.compliant, report.summary);
```
